The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 January is 22,620 (2,618.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 January, there were 5,557 new confirmed cases (643.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 December, there were 2,678 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 108% (2,879 extra cases).
